com.xatkit.core.interpreter.operation.object

Class ArithmeticOperation

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.xatkit.core.interpreter.operation.object.ArithmeticOperation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Operation
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GreaterOperation, GreaterOrEqualOperation, LesserOperation, LesserOrEqualOperation

    public abstract class ArithmeticOperation
extends Object
implements Operation
    A generic arithmetic operation.

    This abstract class contains common behavior reused by all the concrete arithmetic operations (in particular source and args checks). The core logic of subclasses' operations is implemented in the doOperation(Integer, Integer) method.

    • Method Detail

      • invoke

        public final Object invoke(Object source,
                           List<Object> args)
        Computes the ArithmeticOperation over the provided source and args.

        This method performs generic checks reused by concrete arithmetic operations. The core logic of subclasses' operations is implemented in the doOperation(Integer, Integer) method.

        This method checks that the provided source is an Integer instance, and that the provided args list contains a single element which is also an Integer instance.

        Specified by:
        invoke in interface Operation
        Parameters:
        source - the Object to invoke the Operation on
        args - the arguments of the operation to invoke
        Returns:
        the result of the arithmetic operation
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the provided source, args, or args's first element is null
        IllegalArgumentException - if the provided source or args's first element is not an Integer instance

      • doOperation

        protected abstract Object doOperation(@Nonnull
                                      Integer source,
                                      @Nonnull
                                      Integer target)
        The concrete arithmetic operation to compute.

        This method is extended by concrete subclasses to define the operation's logic. Note that this method takes two Integer instances as parameters.

        Parameters:
        source - the source of the arithmetic operation to perform
        target - the target of the arithmetic operation to perform
        Returns:
        the result of the arithmetic operation
